objects.name: Cloaked Ursa
objects.description: Cloaked Ursa, also known as Cozy Duke and APT 29, is a threat group that has long been considered to be affiliated with the Russian government. This aligns with the group’s historic targeting focus, dating back to malware campaigns against Chechnya and other former Soviet bloc countries in 2008. In recent years, the hack of the United States Democratic National Committee (DNC) in 2016 has been attributed to this group, as well as the SolarWinds supply chain compromises in 2020. Increasing the specificity of the attribution, both the United States and the United Kingdom have publicly attributed this group to Russia’s Foreign Intelligence Service (SVR).

MiniDionis Campaign
objects.description: Unit 42 has uncovered a new campaign from the Cloaked Ursa threat actors, leveraging malware that appears to be related to the Seaduke malware described earlier this week by Symantec. This campaign, which began on July 7, 2015, appears to be targeted at government organizations and think tanks located in democratic countries and utilizes compromised, legitimate websites for spear phishing and command and control activity.

objects.name: Google Drive used to Deliver Cobalt Strike
objects.description: On May 13, 2022, Cluster25 published a report that outlined Cloaked Ursa’s inclusion of DropBox services in their malware campaigns for the first time. Searching for similar techniques, we have seen the actors continue to evolve their tactics, including by incorporating popular online storage services such as Google Drive in their campaigns.
